@startuml UC_09_Notification
' ============================================================
' USE CASE DIAGRAM - MODULE 9: Notification System
' Cross-module Notification Management
' ============================================================

title **Use Case Diagram - Module 9\nNotification System**

left to right direction
skinparam actorStyle awesome
skinparam usecase {
    BackgroundColor #E0F7FA
    BorderColor #00838F
    FontSize 12
    ArrowColor #00838F
}

' === ACTORS ===
actor "User\n(All Roles)" as User #LightBlue
actor "System\n(Auto-trigger)" as System #LightGray

' === SYSTEM BOUNDARY ===
rectangle "Module 9: Notification System" {

    usecase "**UC-9.1: Create Notification**\n---\nSystem auto-creates when:\n- Event approved/rejected\n- Order confirmed\n- New chat message\n- New support ticket\n- Account status changed" as UC_CREATE

    usecase "**UC-9.2: View Notifications**\n---\nBell icon 🔔 shows unread count.\nDropdown list sorted by date.\nFilter: unread only." as UC_VIEW

    usecase "**UC-9.3: Mark as Read**\n---\nClick notification →\nmark isRead=true.\nReduce unread counter." as UC_READ

    usecase "**UC-9.4: Mark All as Read**\n---\nBatch update all\nunread → read.\nOne-click action." as UC_READALL
}

' === ASSOCIATIONS ===
System --> UC_CREATE

User --> UC_VIEW
User --> UC_READ
User --> UC_READALL

' === NOTES ===
note right of UC_CREATE
  **FR-40**
  Notification Types:
  - EVENT_APPROVED
  - EVENT_REJECTED
  - EVENT_PENDING
  - ORDER_CONFIRMED
  - NEW_MESSAGE
  - NEW_SUPPORT_TICKET
  - TICKET_RESPONSE
  - ACCOUNT_BANNED
end note

note right of UC_VIEW
  **FR-41**
  Each notification has:
  - type (enum)
  - message (text)
  - relatedEventId (nullable)
  - relatedOrderId (nullable)
  - isRead (boolean)
  - createdAt
end note

@enduml
